<p>The <code>switch</code> tag provides a rotating switch that cycles through options on each call.</p>

<h2>Basic Switch (Odd/Even)</h2>
<pre>{open}switch 'row', 'odd', 'even'{close}</pre>
<p>Calling switch 'row' multiple times:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Call 1: {switch 'row', 'odd', 'even'}</li>
  <li>Call 2: {switch 'row', 'odd', 'even'}</li>
  <li>Call 3: {switch 'row', 'odd', 'even'}</li>
  <li>Call 4: {switch 'row', 'odd', 'even'}</li>
</ul>

<h2>Three-Way Switch</h2>
<pre>{open}switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'{close}</pre>
<p>Cycling through colors:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Call 1: <span style="color:{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}">{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}</span></li>
  <li>Call 2: <span style="color:{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}">{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}</span></li>
  <li>Call 3: <span style="color:{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}">{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}</span></li>
  <li>Call 4: <span style="color:{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}">{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}</span></li>
  <li>Call 5: <span style="color:{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}">{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}</span></li>
  <li>Call 6: <span style="color:{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}">{switch 'color', 'red', 'green', 'blue'}</span></li>
</ul>

<h2>Use Case: Alternating Row Styles</h2>
<pre>&lt;table&gt;
  {open}sequence '1..5'{close}
    &lt;tr class="{open}switch 'tablerow', 'odd', 'even'{close}"&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;Row {open}$value{close}&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  {open}/sequence{close}
&lt;/table&gt;</pre>
<table>
  {sequence '1..5'}
    <tr class="{switch 'tablerow', 'odd', 'even'}">
      <td>Row {$value}</td>
    </tr>
  {/sequence}
</table>
